President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Utah due to flooding that occurred between April 18 and July 16, 2011. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected area. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. W. Craig Fugate, the Administrator of FEMA, has appointed Mark H. Landry as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.